	filename img/drawing.svg
	scale 50

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In asymmetric or 
\emph on
skewed
\emph default
 distributions, the mean, median, and mode are not all equal.
 Folplowing this idea, there are two types of skewed distributions - positively
 skewed (
\begin_inset Formula $mean\leq median\leq mode$
\end_inset

) and negatively skewed (
\begin_inset Formula $mode\leq median\leq median$
\end_inset

).
 Note that in these inequalities, both equalities can never hold simultaneously.
\end_layout

