\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 is neither too large (
\begin_inset Formula $P\nrightarrow1$
\end_inset

), nor too small (
\begin_inset Formula $P\nrightarrow0$
\end_inset

), for a large 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $n\rightarrow\infty$
\end_inset

.
 Thus for a variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X\sim B(n,P)$
\end_inset

, we define another variable
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z=\frac{X-nP}{\sqrt{nPQ}}=\frac{X-\mu}{\sigma}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Under the limiting conditions, 
\begin_inset Formula $X\sim N(\mu,\sigma^{2})$
\end_inset

 whereas 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\sim N(0,1)$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

's distribution is also called 
\emph on
standard normal 
\emph default
distribution - the mean is 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 and variance is 1.
 The probability functions are
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\phi(Z) & = & \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}Z^{2}}\\
f(X) & = & \frac{1}{\sigma\sqrt{2\pi}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}\big(\frac{X-\mu}{\sigma}\big)^{2}}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Important definite integrals involving 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(Z)$
\end_inset

 are
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int_{z=0}^{1.645}\phi(Z=z)dz=0.45
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
